bit_field.name: STIMENA
bit_field.description: For bit STIMENA[n], in register ITM_TERx: 0 = Stimulus port (32x + n) disabled 1 = Stimulus port (32x + n) enabled

bit_field.name: PRIVMASK
bit_field.description: Bit mask to enable tracing on ITM stimulus ports: Bit [0] = stimulus port [7:0] Bit [1] = stimulus port [15:8] Bit [2] = stimulus port [23:16] Bit [3] = stimulus port [31:24]

bit_field_value.name: TCR_SWOENA_0b0
bit_field_value.description: Timestamp counter uses the processor system clock.

bit_field_value.name: TCR_SWOENA_0b1
bit_field_value.description: Timestamp counter uses asynchronous clock from the TPIU interface.

bit_field.name: TSPrescale
bit_field.description: Local timestamp prescaler, used with the trace packet reference clock.

bit_field.name: GTSFREQ
bit_field.description: Global timestamp frequency. Defines how often the ITM generates a global timestamp, based on the global timestamp clock frequency, or disables generation of global timestamps.

bit_field_value.name: TCR_GTSFREQ_0b01
bit_field_value.description: Generate timestamp request whenever the ITM detects a change in global timestamp counter bits [47:7]. This is approximately every 128 cycles.

bit_field_value.name: TCR_GTSFREQ_0b10
bit_field_value.description: Generate timestamp request whenever the ITM detects a change in global timestamp counter bits [47:13]. This is approximately every 8192 cycles.

bit_field_value.name: TCR_GTSFREQ_0b11
bit_field_value.description: Generate a timestamp after every packet, if the output FIFO is empty.

bit_field.name: TraceBusID
bit_field.description: Identifier for multi-source trace stream formatting. If multi-source trace is in use, the debugger must write a non-zero value to this field.

bit_field.name: BUSY
bit_field.description: Indicates whether the ITM is currently processing events: 0: ITM is not processing any events. 1: ITM events present and being drained.

bit_field_value.name: TCR_BUSY_0b0
bit_field_value.description: ITM is not processing any events.

bit_field_value.name: TCR_BUSY_0b1
bit_field_value.description: ITM events present and beeing drained.

bit_field.name: WriteAccessCode
bit_field.description: Write Access Code. A write of 0xC5ACCE55 enables further write access to this device. An invalid write will have the affect of removing write access.

bit_field.name: IMP
bit_field.description: Lock mechanism is implemented. This bit always reads 1.

bit_field.name: STATUS
bit_field.description: Lock Status. This bit is HIGH when the device is locked, and LOW when unlocked.

bit_field.name: s8BIT
bit_field.description: Access Lock Register size. This bit reads 0 to indicate a 32-bit register is present.

bit_field.name: JEP106
bit_field.description: JEP106 continuation code.

bit_field.name: c4KB
bit_field.description: 4KB Count

bit_field.name: PartNumber
bit_field.description: Part Number [7:0]

bit_field.name: PartNumber
bit_field.description: Part Number [11:8]

bit_field.name: JEP106_identity_code
bit_field.description: JEP106 identity code [3:0]

bit_field.name: JEP106_identity_code
bit_field.description: JEP106 identity code [6:4]

bit_field.name: CustomerModified
bit_field.description: Customer Modified.

bit_field.name: ComponentClass
bit_field.description: Component class
